LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 1082
Introduced by Storer, 43; Bosn, 25; Jacobson, 42; Kauth, 31.
Read first time January 15, 2026
Committee: Transportation and Telecommunications
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the Nebraska Telecommunications Regulation
2 Act; to amend sections 86-101 and 86-103, Reissue Revised Statutes
3 of Nebraska; to define a term; to provide a duty for
4 telecommunications companies as prescribed; to harmonize provisions;
5 and to repeal the original sections.
6 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB1082 LB1082
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 86-101, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 86-101 Sections 86-101 to 86-166 and sections 3 and 4 of this act
4 shall be known and may be cited as the Nebraska Telecommunications
5 Regulation Act.
6 Sec. 2. Section 86-103, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
7 amended to read:
8 86-103 For purposes of the Nebraska Telecommunications Regulation
9 Act, unless the context otherwise requires, the definitions found in
10 sections 86-104 to 86-121.01 and section 3 of this act apply.
11 Sec. 3. North American Numbering Plan has the same meaning as in 47
12 C.F.R. 52.5, as such regulation existed on January 1, 2026.
13 Sec. 4. A telecommunications company shall have a duty to protect
14 subscribers and customers of the company from receiving unwanted calls or
15 text messages from users of unauthenticated North American Numbering Plan
16 numbers and prevent the fraudulent provision of misleading or inaccurate
17 caller identification information.
18 Sec. 5. Original sections 86-101 and 86-103, Reissue Revised
19 Statutes of Nebraska, are repealed.
